### Valid Parameter Ranges

| Parameter | Valid Range | Description |
|-----------|-------------|-------------|
| **L** | L > 0 | Allosteric constant (default T/R bias) |
| **c** | c > 0 | Affinity ratio (selectivity) |
| **n** | n ≥ 1 | Number of binding sites |
| **α** | α ≥ 0 | Normalized contextual pressure |
| **R̄** | 0 ≤ R̄ ≤ 1 | State probability |

### Interpretation Guide

| Condition | Meaning |
|-----------|---------|
| L > 10 | Strong T-state (conservative) bias |
| L < 0.1 | Strong R-state (progressive) bias |
| c < 1 | Activator (favors R-state) |
| c > 1 | Inhibitor (favors T-state) |
| n_H > 1 | Switch-like cooperativity |
| n_H < 1 | Graded response |

### Suggested Actions

1. **Review parameter values** against valid ranges above
2. **Check for typos** in numeric values
3. **Verify effector concentrations** are non-negative
4. **Ensure port count** matches cooperativity dimensionality

